    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style of textiles, particularly rugs, characterized by a higher pile than other Shirvan rugs. They are flat and tightly woven with a red ground color and the central field dominated by three large hooked octagons, the middle one of which is almost invariably white.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
